## Setup & Running

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+
- PostgreSQL 14+ (or Docker)

### Backend Setup

```bash
# 1. Clone and install
git clone <repo-url>
cd finance-backend
npm install

# 2. Configure environment
cp .env.example .env
# Fill in DATABASE_URL and JWT_SECRET in .env

# 3. Start PostgreSQL (Docker option)
docker run --name financedb \
  -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=yourpassword \
  -e POSTGRES_DB=financedb \
  -p 5432:5432 -d postgres:15

# 4. Run migrations
npx prisma migrate dev

# 5. Seed test data
node prisma/seed.js

# 6. Start the backend server
npm run dev
```

Backend runs at `http://localhost:3000`

Verify: `GET /health` → `{ "status": "ok" }`

### Frontend Setup

```bash
# In a second terminal
cd finance-frontend
npm install

# Configure environment
cp .env.example .env
# VITE_API_URL is already set to http://localhost:3000/api — no change needed

# Start the dev server
npm run dev
```

Frontend runs at `http://localhost:5173`

> Both servers must be running simultaneously. Keep two terminal tabs open in VS Code.

